---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About the Project" description="How Chemistry Without Magic works: history, principles, methodology, and the engineering approach behind the platform.">
  <section class="about">
    <h1 class="about__title">About the Project</h1>

    <div class="about__section">
      <h2>How it started</h2>
      <p>
        This project didn't start as a business idea. It was a practical solution to a specific
        problem — quickly and precisely identify my daughter's gaps in chemistry, and close them
        as efficiently as possible.
      </p>
      <p>
        She was in 9th grade, preparing for the Russian state chemistry exam (OGE).
        The goal was clear — school curriculum and exam readiness.
      </p>
      <p>There are plenty of materials out there. But I ran into problems:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>courses are presented linearly and identically for everyone,</li>
        <li>there's almost no formal measurement of understanding,</li>
        <li>explanations sometimes look like "magic",</li>
        <li>the knowledge structure is blurry.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="about__accent">
        But chemistry is not magic.<br/>
        It is a rigorous model of particles, energy, and the structure of matter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about__section">
      <h2>What didn't work in the traditional format</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Progress is measured by scores, not by skill structure.</li>
        <li>There's no dependency map between topics.</li>
        <li>You can't tell which mistake is fundamental and which is superficial.</li>
        <li>Little attention is paid to causality: why does a reaction proceed this way?</li>
      </ul>
      <p>At some point it became clear: I needed a tool, not just a course.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about__section">
      <h2>So I built my own</h2>
      <p>
        I'm not a chemist by training — I'm an engineer.
        I'm used to thinking in systems, models, and dependencies.
      </p>
      <p>This site is an attempt to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>decompose school chemistry into competencies,</li>
        <li>connect them with dependencies,</li>
        <li>measure understanding via a probabilistic model (BKT),</li>
        <li>select exercises adaptively,</li>
        <li>use standardised exam tasks as a formal verification benchmark.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Content and explanations are generated with the help of AI models.
        This means inaccuracies, errors, and oversimplifications are possible.
        If you spot any — <a href="https://github.com/dronsv/chemistry-no-magic/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">report them on GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about__section">
      <h2>How the project grew</h2>
      <p>
        While building a simple practice tool, I got carried away and started constructing
        a full chemistry ontology: substances, ions, reactions, properties,
        classifications — all connected in a single knowledge graph.
      </p>
      <p>
        On top of the ontology, an automatic task generation engine emerged:
        instead of hand-crafting exercises, the system generates tasks from templates,
        selects distractors, builds explanations, and solves problems through
        derivation chains from formulas.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then came the question: could this work beyond the Russian curriculum?
        That's how multilingual support was born — the platform now works in
        four languages (Russian, English, Polish, Spanish) and supports
        five exam systems (OGE, EGE, GCSE, Matura, EBAU).
      </p>
      <p>
        What started as help for one child turned into an attempt to build
        an open, structured, and adaptive chemistry learning platform —
        no magic, just an engineering approach.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about__section">
      <h2>Methodological principles</h2>
      <div class="principles">
        <div class="principle">
          <strong>1. Chemistry is a system</strong>
          <span>We work with a competency map and its dependencies, not isolated topics.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <strong>2. Understanding is measured</strong>
          <span>A probabilistic skill mastery model is used, not just "solved / didn't solve".</span>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <strong>3. Exams are calibration tools</strong>
          <span>Standardised exam tasks reflect the curriculum and formally verify readiness.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <strong>4. No magic</strong>
          <span>Every rule has an explanation: through electron configurations, electronegativity, structure of matter, and process energetics.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <strong>5. Minimum fluff — maximum structure</strong>
          <span>Model &rarr; examples &rarr; variations &rarr; reinforcement.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about__section about__disclaimer">
      <p>
        This project does not replace school curricula and does not compete with major
        educational platforms. It is an attempt to build a structured, adaptive
        diagnostic and learning tool that can be used alongside official and
        verified resources.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-2xl); }
  .about__title { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl); }
  .about__section { margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
  .about__section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm); }
  .about__section p { color: var(--color-text); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm); }
  .about__section ul { margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm); padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text); line-height: 1.7; }
  .about__section li { margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
  .about__accent { font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.05rem; padding: var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary); border-radius: 0.25rem; margin-top: var(--space-md); }
  .principles { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-sm); }
  .principle { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-xs); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: 0.375rem; }
  .principle strong { font-size: 0.9375rem; }
  .principle span { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .about__disclaimer { padding: var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .about__disclaimer p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0; }
</style>
